My apologies. I didn't mean to interrupt. Please, carry on
without minding me.

DJ: Man, you're so cool! At times like this, you gotta just

Is that so? I'm not quite familiar with the customs of this

battle hymn to inspire the troops.

DJ: HAHAHA! I like you, big newbie! Get me a drink too!
Something that'll make the floor explode with
excitement—counting on you!!

I don't understand words like 'buchiage' or 'puchyohe', but
your dedication to your job is admirable. Should I quickly
give you something that'll lift your spirits? Or should I
choose something that won't strain your throat for work?
DJ: Hey! Hey! Hey!! That's the spirit!!

DJ: I'm the Floor's Tiger! But no spicy stuff for me, okay?
Thanks for being considerate! I like you, so hit me with the
same L size, please!!

Oh! Is that so? You're a good guy! Drink as much as you
want!!
DJ: *gulp*... *gulp*... *gulp*...!
DJ: Higher! Higher! Everybody scream!!!

DJ: Let's keep this party going all night long~~~~~~~~~~
yeahhhhh!!!!
?????? Well, if you're satisfied, then that's good...!!

DJ: Sorry... I'm all for a hype drink, but no spicy stuff,
okay...

DJ: Dragon, you and me, we're like a tiger and a dragon

DJ: Sorry... Tonight's a party night till morning, can't do

DJ: True, it's delicious, but tonight I won't shed tears. 1,

I let my guard down. It's not just about serving popular

and be more considerate.
DJ: So! So! That's the kind of simple stuff I like!!

DJ: *gulp*... *gulp*... smooth...!!

DJ: How you feel? Hands up! Hands up! Put your hands up!

FOOooooooooo!!!!
Hey, you there.
Bunny: What is it?

That customer over there seems to be quite the big spender.
A regular?

Bunny: No, that's not it. She only started coming to our
shop recently, you see~.

Bunny: As you can see, she orders plenty of drinks. And
after that, she always stays in the best room of our hotel
section and plays more.
Oh, that's a good sign for business.

Bunny: That's why when that customer comes in, everyone's
all over her, wanting to serve her. I don't like it because
it drives the other customers away. And her manners are
crude; it's like she's just learned how to play.

Bunny: I don't know the details, but apparently, the
business with the goods she's dealing with has been going
well recently, and she's been living the easy life. It's a
big help to our shop too, but you know...

Thanks for telling me. Sorry to have kept you, go back to
work.

Bunny: If you want her to like you, you better work hard
too~. See ya♪

(I've heard that it's not uncommon for those connected to
the capital's affairs to come here as customers. And as for
that person's circumstances, the profits from the goods
she's dealing with have been good, especially recently.)

(Considering the current state of the capital preparing for
war, it makes sense that the goods in question would be in
demand. The golem we fought earlier was also referred to as
a new type of weapon. And the negotiations take place in
this establishment.)

(There's almost no doubt that she's involved in this matter.
But for now... it's hard to gather any significant
information with so many people around.)

(If I remember correctly, after drinking, she always heads
to her hotel room.)
(If I'm going to strike, that would be the place...──)
